What You Need to Know

The Lifetime Ban Charter Amendment +
Politicians in City Hall are working overtime to take away your rights. They want a lifetime term limits ban on former Mayors and Supervisors. They would ban leaders like Jerry Brown, who served as Governor in the 1970's and then returned after a lifetime of experience to serve California again. It's really a ban on voters' rights.
Solution Looking for a Problem +
They call it "closing a loophole." That's rubbish. Only one San Francisco leader, out of dozens and dozens, has ever returned to serve again. As Governor Brown says, "it is rare for an elected official to serve, leave office, pursue other work, and then decide to run again." We shouldn't gut the San Francisco Charter for a "loophole" that has occurred exactly once.
New and Young Leaders Are Already Emerging +
In 2024, 4 out of 6 candidates elected Supervisor had never held elected office. A new Mayor was elected who was completely new to politics. Voters are already making change happen, and it should be voters – not City Hall incumbent politicians – who decide who serves as our leaders.
Extreme and Anti-Democratic +
71% of the most populous American cities with term limits don't have lifetime bans. In California, just 2 cities – both in deep red, Republican counties – have a lifetime ban. That's because a lifetime ban is both extreme and anti-democratic.

San Francisco has a proud tradition of defending democracy.
Let's do it again by rejecting the lifetime ban.
